page.title: 05KINGSWOOD NEW HOUSING ESTATE
page.content: Probably the greatest change is found at Kingswood. Until post-war years this had few soundly built houses, the majority being wooden frame buildings (shacks) separated from their neighbours by considerable distances in many instances. Today most of these have gone and in their place expensive and attractive houses have been erected. Much of this, however, is outside the coverage of this block. Many of the old houses are being renovated (often at great expense) and are very attractive to look at while retaining their original character. This has been made possible by the sale of woodland from Leeds Castle estate.
